    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 6 @ 2018/2019",
    "Question": {
      "content": "The force of repulsion between two point charges 5µC and 8µC separated at a distance of 0.2m apart is? Given k = 9×10⁹Nm²C⁻²",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "300N",
        "400N",
        "600N",
        "900N"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "900N"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>The force between two point charges is given by <b>Coulomb's Law</b>:</p> \\[ F = k \\frac{|q_1 q_2|}{r^2} \\] <p><b>Given</b>:</p> <ul> <li>Charge 1 (<i>q₁</i>) = 5µC = 5 × 10⁻⁶ C</li> <li>Charge 2 (<i>q₂</i>) = 8µC = 8 × 10⁻⁶ C</li> <li>Distance (<i>r</i>) = 0.2 m</li> <li>Coulomb's constant (<i>k</i>) = 9 × 10⁹ Nm²C⁻²</li> </ul> <p><b>Calculation</b>:</p> \\[ F = (9 × 10⁹) \\frac{|(5 × 10⁻⁶)(8 × 10⁻⁶)|}{(0.2)^2} \\] \\[ F = (9 × 10⁹) \\frac{40 × 10⁻¹²}{0.04} \\] \\[ F = (9 × 10⁹) × 10⁻⁹ \\] \\[ F = 9\\,\\text{N} \\times 100 \\] \\[ F = 900\\,\\text{N} \\] <p>Thus, the correct answer is <b>900N</b>.</p>"
    },
    "topic": [
      "Electromagnetism",
      "Electromagnetism, Coulomb's Law",
      "Electrostatics"
    ]
  }
